{
  "stem": "2170.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They don't have to go into the army so they can have-- because this is what they were doing was just as good as they were in the army.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my brother-in-law organized a big factory with a lot of people working.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the fabrics was given by the government.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The fabrics came from the United States, from England, and they made uniforms for the railroads.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I used to help them out too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I had a job.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I-- you had to have a job already by the Russians and to be reported by the KGB every day, every week.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They give you a black book that if you do anything bad or something, you are responsible what you're doing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So every turn, they have an eye on you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then my father wrote already a letter that he send out affidavits for me to come to the United States with the State Department.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they sent to Moscow to the American Embassy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was already 1945.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In 1945, in May-- no, in July, the end of June/July, I-- yeah, I wrote to the-- the American Embassy wrote me  a letter, which I have it over here.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Moscow.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the ambassador was Averell Harriman.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he wrote me a letter that I have a visa from the State Department to come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But because I'm a Soviet citizen, but I was born in Poland, I have to write to demand from the Polish Embassy in Moscow to get me a Polish passport and a Soviet exit visa, and then I will get the American visa.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But to get all of this, you as a Russian citizen, you have to get permission by the Russian government to come to Moscow.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
